a time there was a farmer’s son whose name was George. He wished so much to be a prince that he would try everything. But it was difficult for him to make out whether there was an ogre, some water-nymphs or other magic-keepers about. One day he went in his father’s wood and began to fell a tree. As he cleft the last branch with his axe, he saw a nut. The nut floated on through the air and fell
